Hudson Bay Capital Management LP Has Lowered Dupont Stk (DD) Position, Webcom Group (WWWW)’s Sentiment Is 0.85

July 26, 2017 - By Vivian Park

Web.com Group, Inc. provides a range of Internet services to small businesses. The company has market cap of $1.17 billion. The Firm operates through Web services and products segment. It has a 112.62 P/E ratio. The Firm offers subscription solutions, including domains, hosting, Website design and management, search engine optimization, online marketing campaigns, local sales leads, social media, mobile products and e-commerce solutions.
Hudson Bay Capital Management Lp decreased Dupont Stk (DD) stake by 44.29% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Hudson Bay Capital Management Lp sold 12,460 shares as Dupont Stk (DD)’s stock rose 0.43%. The Hudson Bay Capital Management Lp holds 15,675 shares with $1.15M value, down from 28,135 last quarter. Dupont Stk now has $74.13 billion valuation. The stock declined 1.32% or $1.13 reaching $84.36 per share. About 959,635 shares traded. E I Du Pont De Nemours And Co (NYSE:DD) has risen 20.82% since July 26, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 4.12% the S&P500.






